title: Google\Cloud\BigQuery\AnalyticsHub\V1\DataExchange
name: DataExchange
description:
A data exchange is a container that lets you share data. Along with the descriptive information about the data exchange, it contains listings that reference shared datasets.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.bigquery.analyticshub.v1.DataExchange

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Output only. The resource name of the data exchange. e.g. projects/myproject/locations/US/dataExchanges/123.

params.name: data.display_name
params.description: Required. Human-readable display name of the data exchange. The display name must contain only Unicode letters, numbers (0-9), underscores (_), dashes (-), spaces ( ), ampersands (&) and must not start or end with spaces. Default value is an empty string. Max length: 63 bytes.

params.name: data.description
params.description: Optional. Description of the data exchange. The description must not contain Unicode non-characters as well as C0 and C1 control codes except tabs (HT), new lines (LF), carriage returns (CR), and page breaks (FF). Default value is an empty string. Max length: 2000 bytes.

params.name: data.primary_contact
params.description: Optional. Email or URL of the primary point of contact of the data exchange. Max Length: 1000 bytes.

params.name: data.listing_count
params.description: Output only. Number of listings contained in the data exchange.

params.name: data.icon
params.description: Optional. Base64 encoded image representing the data exchange. Max Size: 3.0MiB Expected image dimensions are 512x512 pixels, however the API only performs validation on size of the encoded data. Note: For byte fields, the content of the fields are base64-encoded (which increases the size of the data by 33-36%) when using JSON on the wire.
